# .claude/readonly-paths — paths protected from Edit/Write by Claude.
#
# How it works:
#   - Hook .claude/hooks/core/protect-readonly.sh reads this file on every
#     Edit/Write attempt
#   - One pattern per line, literal substring match against the file path
#   - Empty lines and # comments ignored
#   - If this file is empty or absent → hook is a no-op
#
# To activate: copy this template to .claude/readonly-paths and uncomment
# what applies to your project.
#
# Examples (uncomment as needed):

# Raw / unprocessed data — never edit after creation
# data/raw/

# SQLite databases (use migrations or schema scripts, not direct edits)
# data/corpus.db
# data/corpus.db-journal

# Applied DB migrations — once applied, never modify
# migrations/applied/

# Generated artifacts (regenerate via make, don't hand-edit)
# docs/diagrams/classes/
# docs/diagrams/deps/

# Vendored / third-party code
# vendor/
# third_party/
